title: Bug 109350 - Output parameter should display in data set dialog
description: When calling a stored procedure from an Oracle database, the query result is stored in an output parameter as an object. However, while in the query result page, no data is returned. The expected behavior is that the output parameter should display in the edit data set dialog.
OB: While in the query result page, no data is returned.
EB: The output parameter should display in the edit data set dialog.
SR: 1. Call the stored procedure from an Oracle database. 2. Navigate to the query result page. 3. Observe that no data is returned, even though an output parameter exists. 4. Open the edit data set dialog and verify that the output parameter is displayed.
